anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Spotlight is a type of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Light3D","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" node that emits lights in a specific direction, in the shape of a cone. The light is attenuated through the distance. This attenuation can be configured by changing the energy, radius and attenuation parameters of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Light3D"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When using the Mobile rendering method, only 8 spot lights can be displayed on each mesh resource. Attempting to display more than 8 spot lights on a single mesh resource will result in spot lights flickering in and out as the camera moves. When using the Compatibility rendering method, only 8 spot lights can be displayed on each mesh resource by default, but this can be increased by adjusting ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/limits\/opengl\/maxLightsPerObject"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using the Mobile or Compatibility rendering methods, spot lights will only correctly affect meshes whose visibility AABB intersects with the light’s AABB. If using a shader to deform the mesh in a way that makes it go outside its AABB, "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GeometryInstance3D\/extraCullMargin","type":"reference"},{"text":" must be increased on the mesh. Otherwise, the light may not be visible on the mesh.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/SpotLight3D"},"